         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[25 May 1892] ¶  ¶ The enquiry, dear Mr Wilson, whether out of the vote of this quater ¶  anything could be allowed for incidentals, arose from your circular about what could be saved of the votes of ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.05.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">U92/2627, unit 454, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The file includes a typed copy of M's letter, presumable prepared in the Chief Secretary's Office.</p>
               </note>[25 May 1892]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured on photocopy. The typed copy gives the date as 25 May 1892 - check against MS.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The enquiry, dear Mr Wilson, whether out of the vote of this quater<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">quarter?</p>
               </note> anything could be allowed for incidentals, arose from your circular about what could be saved of the votes of the finance-year. As said before, I will bear […]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured on photocopy.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> the […]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured on photocopy.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> books,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">The typed copy has 'As said before, I will bear all the incidentals out of my salary …'. — which leaves out '[…] books' which was interlined, but adds it to the last sentence: 'Museum material, stores, books.'</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Note: the copy all leaves out the underlining.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> incidentals out of my Salary and so the expenses for a messenger &amp;c — only on my little cottage, in which I devote the whole <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">seven rooms</hi>
               </seg> to office-work, is still a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mortgage</hi>
               </seg>. So I feel sad, that the work of the establishment and its researches and communications must be discontinued in several directions Nevertheless I feel <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">grateful</hi>
               </seg> to you for your championship of my cause, and I will <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">spend all I have</hi>
               </seg> to keep up the dignity and efficiency of my service-branch.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to T. Wilson, 29 February 1892 (in this edition as 92-02-29a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Please tell Mr M'Lean that I fully recognize the favor shown me, to remain in the administrative position, and that my only in[…]<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">there is a blot here which might obscure the rest of a word.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The typed copy has 'that my only x <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in urging …'. There is a pencilled note in the margin, hard to read, but which appears to speculate on what M meant to write. Need to check MS.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> urging more support for the department was to maintain the scientific dignity in my branch here and also abrod<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">abroad?</p>
               </note> and to continue on a path of useful discoveries.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I still hope, that the two now temporary officers are left me.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The appointments of James Minchin and Charles H. French had been extended until 30 June 1892; see T. Wilson to M, 22 March 1892 (in this edition as 92-03-22a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Ki]ndly<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured on photocopy.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> remember I have nearly one million sheets of plants.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
